The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 JB Chemicals amp; Pharmaceuticals Ltd has registered a 15.08 per cent increase in net profit for the year ended March 31, 2005 at Rs 59.15 crore compared with Rs 51.04 crore in the previous financial year. The board has recommended a final dividend of Rs 1.40 on a share with a nominal value of Rs 2, thereby taking the total dividend paid out this year to 120 per cent. JB Chemicals has achieved a net sales of Rs 358.09 crore against Rs 300.75 crore in the previous financial year, a growth of 19.06 per cent.

 LG Electronics India (LGEIL) has entered its eighth year of operations this year. During this period, the company?s turnover grew from Rs 125 crore to Rs 20,100 crore. It is eyeing to become a $10-billion (Rs 45,000) company by 2010. LGEIL has set a target to manufacture 20 million handsets in its Pune plant by 2010. 

 Delta Airlines has started its daily flight from Chennai to New York. The airline will fly directly between the two cities via Paris. Delta has appointed 80 flight attendants in Chennai to support this new flight.

 Lucent Technologies and Rotary Club of Calcutta Metropolitan have come together to hold free cataract surgery camps in rural areas. The programme aims at providing treatment and restoring eyesight with IOL implants to 5,555 beneficiaries.

 Sutlej Industries has recorded a 37 per cent increase in net profit to Rs 16 crore for 2004-05, up from Rs 11.60 crore in the previous financial year. The company?s turnover grew 13 per cent to Rs 546 crore compared with Rs 483 crore during the period. Operating profit before interest, depreciation and tax went up to Rs 57.30 crore from Rs 48.30 crore.

 ICICI Lombard General Insurance has reported a 52 per cent rise in net profit from Rs 31.77 crore to Rs 48.35 crore in 2004-05. Its gross written premium has shot up 75 per cent, from Rs 506.72 crore in 2003-04 to Rs 885.16 crore last financial year and the company handled 90,000 claims last year compared with 26,500 claims in the previous year. The general insurer?s market share has inched up to 25 per cent during the fiscal. 

 American Express Platinum Card members will enjoy air travel benefits from Delta Airlines, Emirates, Air New Zealand and Malaysia Airlines. AmEx card members will get a free companion ticket with every purchase of a full-fare ticket on Delta Airlines. 

 Levis Strauss (India) has launched Levis Red Tab Slim Jeans Summer Collection, a denim range for women, in Calcutta. The collection is priced between Rs 1,499 and Rs 1,799.

